The problem is when you call waitForSomething method, run method from Worker did not called yet. you should make some time before calling waitForSomething. something like this
 

    public class Worker extends Thread {
    
        private volatile boolean isAlive;
        private Semaphore sema = new Semaphore(1);
    
        public Worker() {
            try {
                sema.acquire();
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                e.printStackTrace();
            }
        }
    
        @Override
        public void run() {
            isAlive = true;
            sema.release();
            try {
                do {
                    //doSomething
                } while (true);
            } finally {
                isAlive = false;
            }
        }
    
        public void waitForSomething() {
            try {
                sema.acquire();
                if (!isAlive) {
                    throw new IllegalStateException(&quot;Worker is not alive&quot;);
                }
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                e.printStackTrace();
            } finally {
                sema.release();
            }
            //something
        }
    
        public void waitForStartOfDoingSomething() {
            //need to wait isAlive = true.
        }
    }

another workaround which I&#39;m not a fan of, would be to change your scenario

    Worker worker = new Worker();
    worker.start();
    Thread.sleep(500);
    worker.waitForStartOfDoingSomething();
    worker.waitForSomething();

But if I know more about your program I could be more helpful.

You may want to check [CountDownLatch][1] for this purpose.

    private final CountDownLatch latch = new CountDownLatch(1);
    
    public void run() {
      try {
        do {
          //doSomething
        } while (true);
      } finally {
        latch.countDown();
      }
    }
    
    public void waitForSomething() throws InterruptedException {
      latch.await();
      //something
    }

  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/CountDownLatch.html

